name: "Pink Wobbler" by Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
description: [Crayon, colored pencil, Sharpie, and sticker collage on reclaimed cardboard with digital embellishments and color.] Evil has come to play! The Pink Wobbler is a deadly fuzzball, hoping to catch a couple of kids who think he's CUTE---but "cute" is a four-letter word!  ---Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
